news.title: Bandra police file FIR against ex-employees for data theft impacting real estate firm
news.para: The police are investigating the matter based on the complaint, which states that the three suspects have joined a Powai-based real estate company after stealing the data.

news.title: Ultratech re-enters race to buy Orient Cement
news.para: UltraTech’s spokesperson was unavailable for comment. Deepak Khetrapal, MD and CEO of OCL, denied discussions were taking place and any talk of sale plans was a “figment of one’s imagination.”

news.title: India's most versatile Real Estate Marketing specialists eye robust growth!
news.para: In the last few months alone, Square One has rolled out powerful success stories in Pune with projects the likes of Envogue, Shubh Tristar and Majestique Evolvus.

news.title: Leasing of workspace in Jan-Jun up 29% to 33.54 million sq ft: Report
news.para: H1 2024 (January to June) marked the best-ever first half, with leasing volumes at 33.5 million sq ft, surpassing the previous highest H1 performance seen in 2019," the consultant highlighted.

news.title: Institutional investments in real estate up 20% in Apr-June: Colliers
news.para: Institutional investments in industrial & warehousing projects jumped sharply to USD 1,533.1 million during April-June 2024 from USD 133.9 million a year ago.

news.title: NCLAT to wait for lenders' decision on settlement offer from Supertech Realtors
news.para: A three-member NCLAT bench observed that Supertech Realtors submitted an one-time settlement (OTS), and the lead bank principally agreed with the proposal and the proposal is under consideration by the consortium of banks.

news.title: S&P cuts Sweden's SBB rating to selective default
news.para: SBB is at the centre of a Swedish property market bubble that began to unravel in 2022 when inflation and interest rates soared, triggering sharp cuts to its credit ratings and a plunge in its share price.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM directs officials to focus on sand availability
news.para: Due to the policies of the previous government (YSRCP), people are suffering from immense problems. Take measures to immediately resolve them," Naidu directed officials, according to an official press release.

news.title: AIIB to conduct survey for Madurai, Coimbatore metro projects
news.para: According to the recent budget announcement, Detailed Project Reports (DPRs) have been prepared for the metro rail projects. The Coimbatore project, covering Avinashi and Sathyamangalam Road, is estimated to cost Rs 10,740 crore.

news.title: Central government plans to hike rural housing subsidies to over $6.5 billion: Sources
news.para: The government is worried over widespread rural economic distress, driven by higher food inflation and sluggish growth in farmers' incomes," said one of the government sources with knowledge of budget discussions.

news.title: Bihar CM asks officials to complete land survey by July 2025
news.para: Now with the appointment of 9,888 more officials, the department must complete the special survey and settlement of lands across the state by July 2025.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP collects property tax worth Rs 1,646 crore in April-June 2024
news.para: It has collected Rs 1,646 crore in property tax till June 29 this financial year, whereas the amount for the April-June period last year was Rs 2,287 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra issues government resolution for Kamathipura redevelopment
news.para: Under Regulation 33(9) (cluster redevelopment) of Development Control Promotion and Regulations (DCPR)-2034, tenants are entitled to free housing and in this case too they will get a minimum of 500-sq-ft flat.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh cabinet passes draft of UP NIRMAN Bill-2024
news.para: The official also said according to draft Bill, at least four such SIRs will be created in UP, which will be in the four geographical areas of the state. He said the state has around 20 thousand acres of land bank available.

news.title: Gujarat RERA freezes over 1,000 project-linked bank accounts
news.para: The move will impact a number of developers in Ahmedabad, Vadodara, Surat and Rajkot as this action prohibits them from advertising or selling remaining units of the projects. Furthermore, the developers can't even seek credit for these projects.

news.title: Emaar India booked for selling green belt plot to Polestar to build school
news.para: Polestar Private Ltd lodged the complaint against Emaar at Sector 65 police station around a month ago. It was sold a 1.2-acre plot in Heritage One society in Sector 62.

news.title: YEIDA plans departmental inquiry against officials in Supertech & Sunworld case
news.para: The Authority is now planning a departmental inquiry against its legal officer and officials of the group housing department for providing misleading information regarding the high court cases involving Supertech and Sunworld.

news.title: Capgemini to invest Rs 1,000 crore to set up six lakh sq ft space in Chennai
news.para: The campus would integrate advanced energy and water-efficient technologies, utilise recycled materials and implement rainwater harvesting during construction.
